Action.c(93):         'use strict';\n
Action.c(93):         services.service('smoothScroll', [function(){\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):             this.scrollTo = function(eID) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):                 var startY = currentYPosition();\n
Action.c(93):                 var stopY = elmYPosition(eID);\n
Action.c(93):                 var distance = stopY > startY ? stopY - startY : startY - stopY;\n
Action.c(93):                 if (distance < 100) {\n
Action.c(93):                     scrollTo(0, stopY); return;\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):                 var speed = Math.round(distance / 100);\n
Action.c(93):                 if (speed >= 20) speed = 20;\n
Action.c(93):                 var step = Math.round(distance / 25);\n
Action.c(93):                 var leapY = stopY > startY ? startY + step : startY - step;\n
Action.c(93):                 var timer = 0;\n
Action.c(93):                 if (stopY > startY) {\n
Action.c(93):                     for ( var i=startY; i<stopY; i+=step ) {\n
Action.c(93):                         setTimeout("window.scrollTo(0, "+leapY+")", timer * speed);\n
Action.c(93):                         leapY += step; if (leapY > stopY) leapY = stopY; timer++;\n
Action.c(93):                     } return;\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):                 for ( var i=startY; i>stopY; i-=step ) {\n
Action.c(93):                     setTimeout("window.scrollTo(0, "+leapY+")", timer * speed);\n
Action.c(93):                     leapY -= step; if (leapY < stopY) leapY = stopY; timer++;\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):                 function currentYPosition() {\n
Action.c(93):                     // Firefox, Chrome, Opera, Safari\n
Action.c(93):                     if (self.pageYOffset) return self.pageYOffset;\n
Action.c(93):                     // Internet Explorer 6 - standards mode\n
Action.c(93):                     if (document.documentElement && document.documentElement.scrollTop)\n
Action.c(93):                         return document.documentElement.scrollTop;\n
Action.c(93):                     // Internet Explorer 6, 7 and 8\n
Action.c(93):                     if (document.body.scrollTop) return document.body.scrollTop;\n
Action.c(93):                     return 0;\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):                 function elmYPosition(eID) {\n
Action.c(93):                     var elm = document.getElementById(eID);\n
Action.c(93):                     var y = elm.offsetTop;\n
Action.c(93):                     var node = elm;\n
Action.c(93):                     while (node.offsetParent && node.offsetParent != document.body) {\n
Action.c(93):                         node = node.offsetParent;\n
Action.c(93):                         y += node.offsetTop;\n
Action.c(93):                     } return y;\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):             };\n
Action.c(93):         }])\n
Action.c(93):     });\n

Action.c(93):                         function configSlider() {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):                             var maxVal;\n
Action.c(93):                             var minVal = 900000;\n
Action.c(93):                             angular.forEach(s.searchResult, function (category) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):                                 var products = category.products\n
Action.c(93):                                 angular.forEach(products, function (product) {\n
Action.c(93):                                     if (product.price < minVal) {\n

Action.c(93):                                         if (!maxVal) {\n
Action.c(93):                                             maxVal = product.price\n
Action.c(93):                                         }\n
Action.c(93):                                     }\n
Action.c(93):                                     else if (product.price > maxVal) {\n
Action.c(93):                                         maxVal = product.price;\n
Action.c(93):                                     }\n
Action.c(93):                                 });\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):                             });\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):                             s.minPriceToFilter = Math.round(minVal) - 1;\n
Action.c(93):                             s.maxPriceToFilter = Math.round(maxVal || 999999);\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):                             slider = document.getElementById('slider');\n
Action.c(93):                             var step = s.maxPriceToFilter - s.minPriceToFilter;\n
Action.c(93):                             step = step < 100 ? 2 : 100;\n
Action.c(93):                             noUiSlider.create(slider, {\n
Action.c(93):                                 start: [s.minPriceToFilter, s.maxPriceToFilter],\n
Action.c(93):                                 connect: true,\n

Action.c(93):                                     'min': s.minPriceToFilter,\n
Action.c(93):                                     'max': s.maxPriceToFilter,\n
Action.c(93):                                 },\n
Action.c(93):                                 step: 1, //step < 100 ? 100 : Math.round(step / 100) - 1,\n
Action.c(93):                                 margin: step,  //Math.round(step / 100) - 1,\n
Action.c(93):                             });\n
Action.c(93):                             slider.noUiSlider.start = s.minPriceToFilter;\n
Action.c(93):                             slider.noUiSlider.end = s.maxPriceToFilter;\n

Action.c(93):     // Value calculation\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// Determine the size of a sub-range in relation to a full range.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction subRangeRatio ( pa, pb ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn (100 / (pb - pa));\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// (percentage) How many percent is this value of this range?\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction fromPercentage ( range, value ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn (value * 100) / ( range[1] - range[0] );\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// (percentage) Where is this value on this range?\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction toPercentage ( range, value ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn fromPercentage( range, range[0] < 0 ?\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tvalue + Math.abs(range[0]) :\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\tvalue - range[0] );\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// (value) How much is this percentage on this range?\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction isPercentage ( range, value ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn ((value * ( range[1] - range[0] )) / 100) + range[0];\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     // Range conversion\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction getJ ( value, arr ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar j = 1;\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\twhile ( value >= arr[j] ){\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tj += 1;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn j;\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// (percentage) Input a value, find where, on a scale of 0-100, it applies.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction toStepping ( xVal, xPct, value ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( value >= xVal.slice(-1)[0] ){\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\treturn 100;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar j = getJ( value, xVal ), va, vb, pa, pb;\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tva = xVal[j-1];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvb = xVal[j];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tpa = xPct[j-1];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tpb = xPct[j];\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn pa + (toPercentage([va, vb], value) / subRangeRatio (pa, pb));\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// (value) Input a percentage, find where it is on the specified range.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction fromStepping ( xVal, xPct, value ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// There is no range group that fits 100\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( value >= 100 ){\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\treturn xVal.slice(-1)[0];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar j = getJ( value, xPct ), va, vb, pa, pb;\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tva = xVal[j-1];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvb = xVal[j];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tpa = xPct[j-1];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tpb = xPct[j];\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn isPercentage([va, vb], (value - pa) * subRangeRatio (pa, pb));\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// (percentage) Get the step that applies at a certain value.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction getStep ( xPct, xSteps, snap, value ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( value === 100 ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\treturn value;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar j = getJ( value, xPct ), a, b;\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// If 'snap' is set, steps are used as fixed points on the slider.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( snap ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\ta = xPct[j-1];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tb = xPct[j];\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t// Find the closest position, a or b.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tif ((value - a) > ((b-a)/2)){\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\treturn b;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\treturn a;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( !xSteps[j-1] ){\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\treturn value;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn xPct[j-1] + closest(\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tvalue - xPct[j-1],\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\txSteps[j-1]\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t);\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n

Action.c(93):     \tfunction handleStepPoint ( i, n, that ) {\n

Action.c(93):     \t\tObject.keys(tests).forEach(function( name ){\n

Action.c(93):     \t\t\tif ( options[name] === undefined && defaults[name] === undefined ) {\n

Action.c(93):     );\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t});\n

Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// Delimit proposed values for handle positions.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction getPositions ( a, b, delimit ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Add movement to current position.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar c = a + b[0], d = a + b[1];\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Only alter the other position on drag,\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// not on standard sliding.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( delimit ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tif ( c < 0 ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\td += Math.abs(c);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tif ( d > 100 ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\tc -= ( d - 100 );\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t// Limit values to 0 and 100.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\treturn [limit(c), limit(d)];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn [c,d];\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// Provide a clean event with standardized offset values.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction fixEvent ( e, pageOffset ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Prevent scrolling and panning on touch events, while\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// attempting to slide. The tap event also depends on this.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\te.preventDefault();\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Filter the event to register the type, which can be\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// touch, mouse or pointer. Offset changes need to be\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// made on an event specific basis.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar touch = e.type.indexOf('touch') === 0,\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tmouse = e.type.indexOf('mouse') === 0,\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tpointer = e.type.indexOf('pointer') === 0,\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tx,y, event = e;\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// IE10 implemented pointer events with a prefix;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( e.type.indexOf('MSPointer') === 0 ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tpointer = true;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( touch ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t// noUiSlider supports one movement at a time,\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t// so we can select the first 'changedTouch'.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tx = e.changedTouches[0].pageX;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\ty = e.changedTouches[0].pageY;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tpageOffset = pageOffset || getPageOffset();\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( mouse || pointer ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tx = e.clientX + pageOffset.x;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\ty = e.clientY + pageOffset.y;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tevent.pageOffset = pageOffset;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tevent.points = [x, y];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tevent.cursor = mouse || pointer; // Fix #435\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn event;\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// Append a handle to the base.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction addHandle ( direction, index ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar origin = document.createElement('div'),\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\thandle = document.createElement('div'),\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tadditions = [ '-lower', '-upper' ];\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( direction ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tadditions.reverse();\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\taddClass(handle, cssClasses[3]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\taddClass(handle, cssClasses[3] + additions[index]);\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\taddClass(origin, cssClasses[2]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\torigin.appendChild(handle);\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn origin;\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// Add the proper connection classes.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction addConnection ( connect, target, handles ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Apply the required connection classes to the elements\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// that need them. Some classes are made up for several\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// segments listed in the class list, to allow easy\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// renaming and provide a minor compression benefit.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tswitch ( connect ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tcase 1:\taddClass(target, cssClasses[7]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t\taddClass(handles[0], cssClasses[6]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t\tbreak;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tcase 3: addClass(handles[1], cssClasses[6]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t\t/* falls through */\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tcase 2: addClass(handles[0], cssClasses[7]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t\t/* falls through */\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tcase 0: addClass(target, cssClasses[6]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t\tbreak;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// Add handles to the slider base.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction addHandles ( nrHandles, direction, base ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar index, handles = [];\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Append handles.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tfor ( index = 0; index < nrHandles; index += 1 ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t// Keep a list of all added handles.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\thandles.push( base.appendChild(addHandle( direction, index )) );\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn handles;\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// Initialize a single slider.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction addSlider ( direction, orientation, target ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Apply classes and data to the target.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\taddClass(target, cssClasses[0]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\taddClass(target, cssClasses[8 + direction]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\taddClass(target, cssClasses[4 + orientation]);\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar div = document.createElement('div');\n
Action.c(93):     \t\taddClass(div, cssClasses[1]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\ttarget.appendChild(div);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn div;\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction addTooltip ( handle, index ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( !options.tooltips[index] ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\treturn false;\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n

Action.c(93):     \t\telement.className = cssClasses[18];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn handle.firstChild.appendChild(element);\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t// The tooltips option is a shorthand for using the 'update' event.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction tooltips ( ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( options.dir ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\toptions.tooltips.reverse();\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Tooltips are added with options.tooltips in original order.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar tips = scope_Handles.map(addTooltip);\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tif ( options.dir ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\ttips.reverse();\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\toptions.tooltips.reverse();\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t}\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\tbindEvent('update', function(f, o, r) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tif ( tips[o] ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\ttips[o].innerHTML = options.tooltips[o] === true ? f[o] : options.tooltips[o].to(r
Action.c(93):     [o]);\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t}\n

Action.c(93):     \t// Get the current step size for the slider.\n
Action.c(93):     \tfunction getCurrentStep ( ) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Check all locations, map them to their stepping point.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Get the step point, then find it in the input list.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\tvar retour = scope_Locations.map(function( location, index ){\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\tvar step = scope_Spectrum.getApplicableStep( location ),\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t// As per #391, the comparison for the decrement step can have some rounding issue
Action.c(93):     s.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t// Round the value to the precision used in the step.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\tstepDecimals = countDecimals(String(step[2])),\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t// Get the current numeric value\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\tvalue = scope_Values[index],\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t// To move the slider 'one step up', the current step value needs to be added.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t// Use null if we are at the maximum slider value.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\tincrement = location === 100 ? null : step[2],\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t// Going 'one step down' might put the slider in a different sub-range, so we\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t// need to switch between the current or the previous step.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\tprev = Number((value - step[2]).toFixed(stepDecimals)),\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t// If the value fits the step, return the current step value. Otherwise, use the\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\t// previous step. Return null if the slider is at its minimum value.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\t\tdecrement = location === 0 ? null : (prev >= step[1]) ? step[2] : (step[0] || fals
Action.c(93):     e);\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t\treturn [decrement, increment];\n
Action.c(93):     \t\t});\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     \t\t// Return values in the proper order.\n
Action.c(93):     \t\treturn inSliderOrder( retour );\n
Action.c(93):     \t}\n

Action.c(93):     /**\n
Action.c(93):      * A directive for adding google places autocomplete to a text box\n
Action.c(93):      * google places autocomplete info: https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javas
Action.c(93):     cript/places\n
Action.c(93):      *\n
Action.c(93):      * Usage:\n
Action.c(93):      *\n
Action.c(93):      * <input type="text"  ng-autocomplete ng-model="autocomplete" options="options" details="
Action.c(93):     details/>\n
Action.c(93):      *\n
Action.c(93):      * + ng-model - autocomplete textbox value\n
Action.c(93):      *\n
Action.c(93):      * + details - more detailed autocomplete result, includes address parts, latlng, etc. (Op
Action.c(93):     tional)\n
Action.c(93):      *\n
Action.c(93):      * + options - configuration for the autocomplete (Optional)\n
Action.c(93):      *\n
Action.c(93):      *       + types: type,        String, values can be 'geocode', 'establishment', '(regions
Action.c(93):     )', or '(cities)'\n
Action.c(93):      *       + bounds: bounds,     Google maps LatLngBounds Object, biases results to bounds, 
Action.c(93):     but may return results outside these bounds\n
Action.c(93):      *       + country: country    String, ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 compatible country code. example
Action.c(93):     s; 'ca', 'us', 'gb'\n
Action.c(93):      *       + watchEnter:         Boolean, true; on Enter select top autocomplete result. fal
Action.c(93):     se(default); enter ends autocomplete\n
Action.c(93):      *\n
Action.c(93):      * example:\n
Action.c(93):      *\n
Action.c(93):      *    options = {\n
Action.c(93):      *        types: '(cities)',\n
Action.c(93):      *        country: 'ca'\n
Action.c(93):      *    }\n
Action.c(93):     **/\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):     angular.module( "ngAutocomplete", [])\n
Action.c(93):       .directive('ngAutocomplete', function() {\n
Action.c(93):         return {\n
Action.c(93):           require: 'ngModel',\n
Action.c(93):           scope: {\n
Action.c(93):             ngModel: '=',\n
Action.c(93):             options: '=?',\n
Action.c(93):             details: '=?'\n
Action.c(93):           },\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):           link: function(scope, element, attrs, controller) {\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):             //options for autocomplete\n
Action.c(93):             var opts\n

Action.c(93):         function soap(options) {\n

Action.c(93):             // a configuration call will not have 'data' specified ('params' is used for backw

Action.c(93):             if (options && !options.params && !options.data) {\n
Action.c(93):                 $.extend(globalConfig, options); // update global config\n
Action.c(93):                 enableLogging = options.enableLogging;\n
Action.c(93):                 log('jQuery.soap - globalConfig updated:', globalConfig);\n
Action.c(93):                 return globalConfig;\n
Action.c(93):             }\n
Action.c(93):             $.extend(config, globalConfig, options);\n
Action.c(93):             // function log will only work below this line!\n
Action.c(93):             enableLogging = config.enableLogging;\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):             log('jquery.soap - config:', config);\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):             // fallbacks for changed properties\n
Action.c(93):             SOAPTool.fallbackDeprecated(config);\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):             var soapObject = SOAPTool.processData({\n
Action.c(93):                 data: config.data,\n
Action.c(93):                 name: (!!config.elementName) ? config.elementName : config.method,\n
Action.c(93):                 context: config.context,\n
Action.c(93):                 prefix: (!!config.namespaceQualifier && !config.noPrefix) ? config.namespaceQu
Action.c(93):     alifier+':' : ''\n
Action.c(93):             });\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):             if (!!config.namespaceQualifier && !!config.namespaceURL) {\n
Action.c(93):                 soapObject.addNamespace(config.namespaceQualifier, config.namespaceURL);\n
Action.c(93):             }\n
Action.c(93):             else if (!!config.namespaceURL) {\n
Action.c(93):                 soapObject.attr('xmlns', config.namespaceURL);\n
Action.c(93):             }\n
Action.c(93):     \n

Action.c(93):                 if (config.envAttributes) {\n
Action.c(93):                     for (var i in config.envAttributes) {\n
Action.c(93):                         soapEnvelope.addAttribute(i, config.envAttributes[i]);\n
Action.c(93):                     }\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):                 // SOAPHeader\n
Action.c(93):                 if (!!config.SOAPHeader) {\n
Action.c(93):                     var soapHeader = SOAPTool.processData({\n
Action.c(93):                         data: config.SOAPHeader,\n
Action.c(93):                         name: 'temp',\n
Action.c(93):                         prefix: ''\n
Action.c(93):                     });\n

Action.c(93):                             soapEnvelope.addHeader(soapHeader);\n
Action.c(93):                         }\n
Action.c(93):                     }\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):                 // WSS\n
Action.c(93):                 if (!!config.wss) {\n
Action.c(93):                     var wssObj = SOAPTool.createWSS(config.wss);\n
Action.c(93):                     // add to WSS Security header to soapEnvelope\n

Action.c(93):                         soapEnvelope.addHeader(wssObj);\n

Action.c(93):                 }\n

Action.c(93):                     config.url += config.method;\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n

Action.c(93):                     if ($.isFunction(config.error)) {\n
Action.c(93):                         config.error.call(this, new SOAPResponse(textStatus, jqXHR));\n
Action.c(93):                     }\n
Action.c(93):                 });\n

Action.c(93):                 var errDeferred = new $.Deferred(),\n
Action.c(93):                     errmsg;\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):                 if (!soapObject) {\n
Action.c(93):                     errmsg = 'jquery.soap - no soapObject';\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n

Action.c(93):                 }\n

Action.c(93):         //Soap request - this is what being sent\n
Action.c(93):         function SOAPEnvelope (soapObject) {\n
Action.c(93):             this.typeOf = "SOAPEnvelope";\n
Action.c(93):             this.prefix = 'soap';\n

Action.c(93):             if (parts[1] === 'Envelope' || parts[1] === 'Body') {\n
Action.c(93):                 this.prefix = parts[0];\n
Action.c(93):                 if (soapObject.attr('xmlns:' + this.prefix) === SOAPTool.SOAP11.namespaceURL)

Action.c(93):                     this.soapConfig = this.SOAP11;\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):                 if (soapObject.attr('xmlns:' + this.prefix) === SOAPTool.SOAP12.namespaceURL) 
Action.c(93):     {\n
Action.c(93):                     this.soapConfig = this.SOAP12;\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):                 // Envelope\n
Action.c(93):                 var env = soapObject.find(this.prefix + ':Envelope');\n
Action.c(93):                 if (env && env.attributes) {\n
Action.c(93):                     for (var i in env.attributes) {\n
Action.c(93):                         this.addAttribute(i, env.attributes[i]);\n
Action.c(93):                     }\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):                 // headers\n
Action.c(93):                 header = soapObject.find(this.prefix + ':Header');\n
Action.c(93):                 if (header && header.children) {\n
Action.c(93):                     for (var j = 0; j < header.children.length; j++) {\n
Action.c(93):                         this.addHeader(header.children[j]);\n
Action.c(93):                     }\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):                 // body\n
Action.c(93):                 body = soapObject.find(this.prefix + ':Body');\n
Action.c(93):                 if (body && body.children) {\n
Action.c(93):                     for (var k = 0; k < body.children.length; k++) {\n
Action.c(93):                         this.addBody(body.children[k]);\n
Action.c(93):                     }\n
Action.c(93):                 } else {\n
Action.c(93):                     for (var l = 0; l < soapObject.children.length; l++) {\n
Action.c(93):                         this.addBody(soapObject.children[l]);\n
Action.c(93):                     }\n
Action.c(93):                 }\n
Action.c(93):             } else {\n
Action.c(93):                 // a soapObject with nothing, mere data\n
Action.c(93):                 this.addBody(soapObject);\n
Action.c(93):             }\n
Action.c(93):         }\n
Action.c(93):     \n
Action.c(93):         SOAPEnvelope.prototype = {\n
Action.c(93):             addAttribute: function(name, value) {\n
Action.c(93):                 this.attributes[name] = value;\n
